events.description: Wow I’ve been working here for 9 months already? It’s been fun guys, but I gotta move on now and do those other things I said I was going to do in my gap year...

events.entry: We move!... Or at least, I do
events.description:
My mom buys a second house. It’s pretty cool. It’s not fully ready yet, but my mom wants to rent my old room out, so I move over...alone. It’s a wacky modernist that resembles a spaceship in the middle of the forest, and I’m the only living here. What was that shrieking noise? Oh, p-probably just the pipes. I spend the days in silence, working and cooking for myself, and head over to the other house for dinner and to spend time with fam.

I also start sleeping and working on the floor due to the lack of furniture. It’s pretty groovy and basically how I do everything now.
I got it. My dream offer. Better than anything I could have ever hoped for. I can finally rest

events.entry: That’s it… I’m taking a gap year
Built my first PC, picked up gaming again for the first time in 6 years
events.description: A little something to ease the pain. A PC had been something I had been saving up for and researching the entire year. What had initially begun as just a way to explore VR became a full-blown obsession of its own. I spent a full day building it, and man, was it a beaut *chef’s kiss*

And there it is! The email saying that my internship in Japan, the one thing I still had to look forward to had been cancelled indefinitely. Not even made remote. Cancelled. I secretly knew it was coming all along, but it still blew big time. Now what??
The news was announced while I was on an overnight shift at the first-aid squad. I watched over instagram as campus exploded in a chaos of howls, mourning, and tomfoolery

phases.description: I got approved to stay on campus to serve as an EMT and witnessed campus at its most barren. It was a pretty surreal experience, having a four-person quad to myself, living in the space we had shared just months before. My only activities consisted of the twice a day pilgrimages to the dining hall to pick up my food to go. And just like that, my sophomore year ended...

It was a strange yet enjoyable time, for many reasons. Once again I was home, in fact, probably the longest I had been home in years. I struggled for hours during the day to complete the microscopic tasks at my internship, and spent my nights exploring VR, catching up on games, and reading. I was also lucky enough to pick up a few new interests, from crab-fishing at the shore to rock-climbing in upstate NY with my roommate Tim.

Oh yeah, and spending time with my family was also nice.

Back at my internship—managed to upgrade it to a paid one. Everything’s the same, only this time it’s recruitment season, and I need to whip myself into shape to stand any chance at getting a summer internship. I pour every spare moment I get into sending out applications, polishing up my resume, and grinding leetcode...lot’s of leetcode. I spend 4-6 hours a day doing coding challenges, and all of my weekends. I wake up, go to work, then do coding practice until I go to sleep. A walk is a luxury. Every night I go to bed dreaming about how amazing it would be if I managed to land any internship and yearn to be released from this mental prison with no end in sight. I get rejection after rejection, until...
